<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1521,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
Comments: Shortly after its description, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[622,751,1521,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[622,641,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[658,751,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ducke, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Ducke" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1206,1225,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1337,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">obsoleta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A." pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="362 - 369" refId="ref18241" refString="Ducke, A. (1910) Zur Synonymie der neotropischen Apidae. (Hym.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 6, 362 - 369." type="journal article" year="1910">Ducke, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This synonymy remained unchanged until now that the 
<typeStatus box="[852,966,1557,1583]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">lectotypes</typeStatus>
of both species were studied in detail. Although superficially similar, both species are valid, so the synonymy proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ducke, A." box="[1072,1227,1593,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="362 - 369" refId="ref18241" refString="Ducke, A. (1910) Zur Synonymie der neotropischen Apidae. (Hym.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 6, 362 - 369." type="journal article" year="1910">Ducke (1910)</bibRefCitation>
must be no longer considered correct.
</paragraph>
